column10:
This game is fun.

Pros:
* It has a solid campaign;
* It has nice PvP modes;
* It has nice Coop modes: Campaign coop and Survival (wave survival);
* It has an in-campaign PvP Invasion (Axis player invades campaign players) (My main game mode).
Cons:
* The game DLCs are expensive;
* The Lens glint in PvP (game balancing) is not fun at all. The stealth element we expect from a sniper game is missing.

Bigger maps, not that big, you can take a max 600 meter shot if you are very lucky to spot a target that far, normally you will take shot fom about 400m; Movements more natural; Non lethal shots now do something, the enemy feels the bullet, shoot his arm and he will be able to only hold a pistol; Bullet drop and windage feels more realistic (no more missed shots from 100 meters due to wind lol); You can switch to first person view (iron sights view). The AI, well, if you played SE4 you know what to expect but one thing they added and i liked was the ability of the AI to see your scope glint; Enemy's combat dialogue is much more immersive, plus the soundtrack which is different on each mission.

Now the bad, really bad: 
All dlcs mission suck big time; 
They made the mosin nagant a paid dlc and even so it is a poor weapon compared to the kar98k and springfield; 
Every patch is about 50 Gb and you have to wait for it to download. By the way, everytime a patch is released it introduces more bugs by fixing others, it is like there was no play test;
Few enemies on the maps to keep your busy;

update 11/04/2023: guess what? They released a patch that prevents EVERYONE from playing the game, it simple does not go past the Rebellion logo!

update 07/11/2023: So this is the end, final content was released. No M1 garand; they made us pay for the Mosin Nagant; Frankly, dlc missions that are no better than some main ones, plus overpriced; Pre-downloaded dlcs that you can't get rid of them even if you don't own them.

HEYYYYYY....I've been waiting for this for some time now i'm not gonna explain it all in detail but let me cut to the chase, it's a pretty good game with the story and new AXIS INVASION MODE being pretty cool the game play is decent ( I just wish you could move around more) and the graphics are good as always. 
                { FINAL ---- RATING }

                           (8/10)
